Class ConcatenatedPrimitiveSink<T extends com.google.common.hash.PrimitiveSink>

java.lang.Object
  com.clarkparsia.common.hash.ConcatenatedPrimitiveSink<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.common.hash.PrimitiveSink, java.lang.Iterable<T>
public final class ConcatenatedPrimitiveSink<T extends com.google.common.hash.PrimitiveSink>
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.google.common.hash.PrimitiveSink, java.lang.Iterable<T>

An implementation of PrimitiveSink which has a number of 'child' sinks to which each call to this Sink is delegated. Intended to make it easy to multiplex results to a list of sinks.

Since:
2.3
Version:
2.3
Author:
Michael Grove
